# Environment variables example for UOM-BIT-GPA-
# Rename this file to `.env.local` for local development or to `.env` if you prefer.
# Do NOT commit your real `.env` to the repo — this repository's `.gitignore` already ignores `.env*`.

# Google Analytics (GA4) Measurement ID (client-visible)
# Format: G-XXXXXXXXXX
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# Canonical site URL (used for building absolute links or sending page_location)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://your-site-domain.example

# Optional: CountAPI or other tracking keys (only if you use a private namespace)
#COUNTAPI_KEY=your_countapi_key_here

# Optional: feature flags or other public config
#NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_X=true

# Notes:
# - Next.js will load `.env.local` and `.env` depending on environment. Using `NEXT_PUBLIC_`
#   prefix exposes values to client-side code — this is intentional for GA.
# - For production (Vercel) DO NOT use this file. Instead set variables in the Vercel project
#   settings (Project → Settings → Environment Variables).